default1. Is cycling safe?default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThe 
defaultrate of cyclist fatalities has
default fallen dramatically in recent years. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultSerious injury rat
defaultes have
default also fallen
default. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultAlthough it is possible to draw some conclusions from deaths over the medium term, it is much harder to draw any conclusions from relatively short-term events. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultLondon’s cycle casualty rat
defaultes are comparable to, or better than, most equivalent foreign cities, though exact comparisons are difficult. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThe concept of “subjective safety” is sometimes employed to argue against these empirical truths. We acce
defaultpt the importance of this.  
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultSome objective and empirical signs are also causing us growing concern.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultCycling is far more likely to prolong your life than to end it; an
defaultd more likely to improve your health than to harm it.  
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultCycling will even prolong other people’s lives. 
