defaultThere is a need to raise the quality of the debate. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultWe fear that the all-consuming focus on cycling deaths may be deterring cyclists. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultBy the ve
defaultry act of trying to help cyclists, we are treated as if we have nationalised every accident.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultSome of the assumptions in the debate are wrong.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultEven the best infrastructure in the world cannot remove the responsibility to behave safely, or entirely immunise cyclists against harm
default. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultWe do not say that people should stop talking about safety. It is the number one deterrent to taking up cycling. 
