defaultThere are two different ways of measuring cycle use. “Journeys” are where all or part of the journey was made by bike. “Trips” (about 181 million in London in 2011) are where the entire journey was made by bike. For instance, cycling to the station to get 
defaulta train would count towards the first figure but not the second. 
